      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:97:14",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كَانَ أَبِي ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ وَ أَيُّ شَيْ‏ءٍ أَقَرُّ لِعَيْنِي مِنَ التَّقِيَّةِ إِنَّ التَّقِيَّةَ جُنَّةُ الْمُؤْمِنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Jameel Bin Salih, from Muhammad Bin Marwan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘My<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup> was saying: ‘And which thing is more delighting to my<sup>asws</sup> eyes than the dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>). The dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>) is a shield of the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momin</span>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "14. Ali has narrated from his father from ibn Mahbub from Jamil ibn Salih from Muhammad ibn Marwan from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “My father (a.s.) has said, ‘What could be more delightful to me than al-Taqiyyah’, it is a shield for believing people.’” "
        ]
      }
